===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|dett}}, from {{der|en|fro|dete}} ({{cog|fr|dette}}), from {{der|en|ML.|dēbita}}, from {{der|en|la|dēbitum||what is owed, a debt, a duty}}, neuter of {{m|la|dēbitus}}, perfect passive participle of {{m|la|dēbeō||I owe}}, contraction of {{m|la|*dehibeō||I have from}}, from {{m|la|de||from}} + {{m|la|habeō||I have}}.

The unpronounced "b" in the modern English spelling is a [[Latinisation]] from the Latin etymon {{m|la|dēbitum}}.

